{
  "name": "03 - Webhook Auth (Basic, Header, JWT)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Webhook Authentication\n\nn8n's Webhook node supports several auth modes.\nThis workflow demos the 3 you'll actually use:\n\n1. **Basic Auth** — username + password\n2. **Header Auth** — custom header (e.g. x-api-key)\n3. **JWT Auth** — signed token, enterprise-grade\n\nEach row below has TWO parts:\n→ Left: the protected webhook (server side)\n→ Right: a manual trigger that calls it (client side)\n\nWrong credentials = 403. Try it.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 900,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-32, -400],
      "id": "sticky-intro",
      "name": "Intro"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 1. Basic Auth\n\n**When to use:** quick internal tools, prototypes, trusted networks.\n**Security:** weakest of the three. Credentials sent on every request (base64, NOT encrypted — only safe over HTTPS).\n**Real example:** internal admin webhooks, dev tools.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-32, 0],
      "id": "sticky-basic",
      "name": "Basic Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "auth-basic-demo",
        "authentication": "basicAuth",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2.1,
      "position": [-16, 304],
      "id": "wh-basic",
      "name": "Webhook (Basic Auth)",
      "webhookId": "auth-basic-demo"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"auth\": \"basic\",\n  \"message\": \"Authenticated via Basic Auth\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1.4,
      "position": [208, 304],
      "id": "resp-basic",
      "name": "Respond Basic"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [496, 304],
      "id": "trig-basic",
      "name": "Test Basic"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://YOUR-N8N/webhook/auth-basic-demo",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpBasicAuth",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "{\n  \"hello\": \"basic\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.3,
      "position": [704, 304],
      "id": "http-basic",
      "name": "Call Basic Webhook"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 2. Header Auth\n\n**When to use:** the standard for SaaS webhooks (Stripe, Shopify, Evolution API, etc.)\n**Security:** good. Single secret in a custom header (e.g. x-api-key).\n**Real example:** WhatsApp Evolution API, Telegram bot secrets, most third-party integrations.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 7
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-32, 624],
      "id": "sticky-header",
      "name": "Header Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "auth-header-demo",
        "authentication": "headerAuth",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2.1,
      "position": [-16, 928],
      "id": "wh-header",
      "name": "Webhook (Header Auth)",
      "webhookId": "auth-header-demo"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"auth\": \"header\",\n  \"message\": \"Authenticated via Header Auth\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1.4,
      "position": [208, 928],
      "id": "resp-header",
      "name": "Respond Header"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [496, 928],
      "id": "trig-header",
      "name": "Test Header"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://YOUR-N8N/webhook/auth-header-demo",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "{\n  \"hello\": \"header\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.3,
      "position": [704, 928],
      "id": "http-header",
      "name": "Call Header Webhook"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 3. JWT Auth\n\n**When to use:** enterprise integrations, when payloads must be cryptographically signed, expiring tokens.\n**Security:** strongest. Token can encode user/scope/expiry and is verified against a secret or JWKS.\n**Real example:** B2B APIs, internal microservice mesh, signed third-party callbacks.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-32, 1248],
      "id": "sticky-jwt",
      "name": "JWT Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "auth-jwt-demo",
        "authentication": "jwtAuth",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2.1,
      "position": [-16, 1552],
      "id": "wh-jwt",
      "name": "Webhook (JWT Auth)",
      "webhookId": "auth-jwt-demo"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"auth\": \"jwt\",\n  \"message\": \"Authenticated via JWT\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1.4,
      "position": [208, 1552],
      "id": "resp-jwt",
      "name": "Respond JWT"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [496, 1552],
      "id": "trig-jwt",
      "name": "Test JWT"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://YOUR-N8N/webhook/auth-jwt-demo",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {"name": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer YOUR_SIGNED_JWT_HERE"}
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "{\n  \"hello\": \"jwt\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.3,
      "position": [704, 1552],
      "id": "http-jwt",
      "name": "Call JWT Webhook"
    }
  ],
